editorialNotes.standard: See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.

editorialNotes.standard: Once again, the creators of The Human Body and Simple Machines have turned playtime into a rich learning experience. Tinybopâs sandbox-style app lets kids experiment to their heartsâ contentâseeing what happens when they move the sun, whip up winds, and cause rainstorms. A zoomed-out view illustrates the broader water cycle at work, while fascinating closeups show things like the effects of changing temperatures and strengthening tornadoes on everyday life. We also dig the detailed study guide offering extra info and discussion ideas.

Genetics can be tricky to explain, even for us so-called adults. DNA Play gently introduces kids to the concepts of cellular building blocks, letting youngsters create goofy monsters and mutate them on the fly by swapping around their genetic code. Itâs great simply as a charming, colorful puzzle game to entertain the little ones, but has the added bonus of educating and enlightening budding young scientists.
